[src:radon-transform/funk-transform] Alternatively, Λ2**R**3 can be identified with **R**3 in an SL(3,**R**)-invariant manner, and so the Funk transform *F* maps smooth even homogeneous functions of degree −2 on **R**3\{0} to smooth even homogeneous functions of degree −1 on **R**3\{0}.
[src:radon-transform/funk-transform] The Funk-Radon transform is used in the Q-Ball method for Diffusion MRI introduced by Tuch (2004).
